lead_paragraph: The Legislature approved a bill on Wednesday to move up California's Presidential primary by more than two months, aiming to give the state a more decisive role in Presidential campaigns. Under the legislation, California's Presidential primary would be held on the fourth Tuesday in March instead of in early June. The bill was approved by a vote of 62 to 12 in the Assembly. The Senate passed the measure last week.

headline.main: Bill for Earlier Primary Passes in California
